<HEADLINE>
NTU GRADUATES FAVORITE HIRES AMONG LOCAL FIRMS: SURVEY
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, April 17 (CNA) 04/17/07  21:58:48 (NTU) have replaced
those from National Cheng Kung University (NCKU) (By Elisa Kao)
</P>
<P>
Graduates from National Taiwan University as the favorite new
hires among local enterprises, according to the results of a poll
released Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The survey, conducted by Cheers magazine from March 5 to April 4,
questioned the country's top 1,000 enterprises to find out about
their corporate practices and hiring preferences.
</P>
<P>
NTU graduates exceeded for the first time in 10 years their NCKU
counterparts as the most sought-after workers by local
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The magazine executives attributed the change to the abilities of
NTU graduates in various fields.
</P>
<P>
Lee Chu-ying, who is responsable for the survey, noted that the
corporations' demands for their workers have shifted from
focusing only on specialist skills to also gauging their ability
in other related spheres.
</P>
<P>
National Chiao Tung University graduates came third in the
rating, followed by National Tsinghua University, National
Chengchi University, National Taiwan University of Science and
Technology, Tamkang University, National Sun Yat-sen University,
National Taipei University of Technology and National Central
University.
</P>
<P>
Tamkang University is the only private university to make the top
10 list.
</P>
<P>
The poll results show that many enterprises hope people in their
20s can strengthen their stability and ability to endure stress.
However, some corporations admire new graduates' ability to
express themselves.
</P>
<P>
In addition, more and more corporations require higher education
levels for their employees, with 20 percent of those surveyed
saying they will give preference to graduates with master's
degrees.
</P>
